description:
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a suitably qualified HCPC state registered Biomedical Scientist with a minimum of 3 years post registration experience to join our busy Microbiology team based within the hospital setting at Princess Alexandra Hospital in Harlow Essex.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The department currently processes 270,000 samples per annum including a serology section, which is partly integrated with the Biochemistry department for the use of the Abbott Alinity analysers. The laboratory is also equipped with a BacTalert 3D, , Autoscan, Bruker Maldi-tof, IQ 200 automated urine microscopy analyser, Mast Urisystem, Roche COBAS 4800 for CT/NG dual PCR testing, Aus Diagnostics platform and VIDAS serology analyser. The laboratory is ISO 15189 UKAS accredited.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Good organisational and communication skills will be required along with up-to-date knowledge of microbiology. You should have enthusiasm and have the ability to work on your own or as part of a team. You are required to train more junior members of the team and play supportive role to the Senior BMS’. You will be responsible for maintaining a high standard of professional expertise and quality.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be encouraged to maintain professional and personal development and will be expected to participate in a single disciplinary on call service when appropriate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Registration with the Health Professions Council as a Biomedical Scientist.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Specialist Diploma in Microbiology/Virology or equivalent.(for band 6)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Continual professional development and maintenance of up to date knowledge of new technologies and methodologies is required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;3 years post registration experience in Microbiology (for band 6)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameDebbie OrrissJob titleMicrobiology Laboratory ManagerTelephone number01279 444455 x7138 or 2726&lt;/p&gt;
